Privacy Policy for Word Counter

Last updated: May 30, 2026

Word Counter (the "App", "we", "us", or "our") is developed by [Your Name / Company Name]. This Privacy Policy explains how the App handles your information. We do not collect or sell your personal content — the text you write stays on your device. The App is free and supported by third-party advertising, as described below.

SUMMARY
- We do not require an account or login.
- Your documents, notes, statistics, and settings are stored locally on your device.
- The App is free and supported by ads provided by Google AdMob.
- Our advertising partner may collect device identifiers and usage data to serve ads (see "Advertising").
- We do not sell your personal content.

INFORMATION WE DO NOT COLLECT
We (the developer) do not collect, transmit, or sell personally identifiable information such as your name, email address, or the documents and text you write. Your written content stays on your device.

INFORMATION STORED ON YOUR DEVICE
To provide its features, the App stores the following only on your device, in the App's private local storage:
- The text, documents, and notes you create.
- Writing statistics and daily activity generated within the App.
- Your writing goals and app preferences (such as theme).
This data never leaves your device unless you choose to share or export it. Uninstalling the App permanently deletes this data.

ADVERTISING
The App is free and is supported by advertising provided by Google AdMob, a service of Google LLC. To serve and measure ads, AdMob and its partners may collect and process certain information, which may include:
- Your device's advertising identifier (Advertising ID).
- IP address, device type, operating system, and general (coarse) location derived from your IP.
- App usage and ad interaction data.
This information is collected and used by Google in accordance with Google's Privacy Policy (https://policies.google.com/privacy) and "How Google uses information from sites or apps that use our services" (https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites). You can reset or delete your Advertising ID and opt out of personalized ads at any time in Settings > Privacy > Ads on your device. You may still see non-personalized ads.

PERMISSIONS
The App may request the following permissions, used only for the stated purpose:
- Microphone (RECORD_AUDIO): Used only when you tap the voice/dictation button to convert your speech to text. Audio is processed by your device's speech recognition service and is not recorded, stored, or transmitted by us.
- Storage / Media access: Used only when you choose to import a text file or export/save your text, through your device's system file picker. The App only accesses the specific files you select.
- Internet: Required to display ads and for standard system functionality. Your documents and personal text are not uploaded to our servers.

VOICE INPUT AND READ-ALOUD
The voice typing (speech-to-text) and read-aloud (text-to-speech) features rely on services provided by your device's operating system (for example, Google's speech services on Android). When you use these features, your audio or text may be processed by that system service to perform the conversion. This processing is governed by the privacy policy of your device or operating-system provider. We do not control, receive, or store this data.

THIRD-PARTY SERVICES
The App uses the following third-party services, which may collect information as described in their privacy policies:
- Google AdMob (advertising) — https://policies.google.com/privacy
- Your device's built-in speech recognition and text-to-speech services.
The App does not include any other third-party analytics or tracking SDKs.

DATA SHARING AND SELLING
We do not sell your personal content. Information collected by our advertising partner (Google) is handled under Google's own privacy policy.

DATA SECURITY
Your documents are stored locally on your device, so their security depends on your device's own security measures. We recommend using a screen lock and keeping your device's software up to date.

CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
The App is intended for a general audience and is not directed at children under 13. Because the App displays third-party ads that may use advertising identifiers, we do not knowingly direct the App to, or collect information from, children under 13. If you believe a child has provided information through the ad services, please contact us.

YOUR CHOICES AND DATA DELETION
You are in full control of your content. You can delete individual documents within the App, or remove all App data by uninstalling the App. You can reset or opt out of advertising personalization in your device settings as described under "Advertising."

CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date.
